crossDbId.description: the unique identifier for a cross

crossName.description: the human readable name for a cross

germplasmDbId.description: The ID which uniquely identifies a germplasm

germplasmName.description: Name of the germplasm. It can be the preferred name and does not have to be unique.

locationDbId.description: The ID which uniquely identifies a location, associated with this study

locationName.description: The human readable name of a location associated with this study

observationUnitDbId.description:
The ID which uniquely identifies an observation unit

MIAPPE V1.1 (DM-70) Observation unit ID - Identifier used to identify the observation unit in data files containing the values observed or measured on that unit. Must be locally unique.

observationUnitName.description: A human readable name for an observation unit

observationUnitPUI.description:
A Permanent Unique Identifier for an observation unit

MIAPPE V1.1 (DM-72) External ID - Identifier for the observation unit in a persistent repository, comprises the name of the repository and the identifier of the observation unit therein. The EBI Biosamples repository can be used. URI are recommended when possible.

programDbId.description: The ID which uniquely identifies a program

programName.description: The human readable name of a program

seedLotDbId.description: The unique identifier for the originating Seed Lot

seedLotName.description: A human readable name for the originating Seed Lot

studyDbId.description: The ID which uniquely identifies a study within the given database server

studyName.description: The human readable name for a study

trialDbId.description: The ID which uniquely identifies a trial

trialName.description: The human readable name of a trial
